steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"8p0qk","text":"We cultured epilithic biofilms in K medium (Keller et al. 1987) on a cover glass slide inside a Polycarbonate cell culture plate of 6-Wells, for one week.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"24qrm","text":"During nocturnal low tides, we collected animals of each mollusk species from wave-exposed platforms, brought them to the laboratory in coolers, and then placed them to acclimatize for a week in separate aquariums by circulating seawater and constant aeration.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"abupb","text":"The pedal mucus was collected under a laminar flow cabinet (Connor 1986). Animals were carefully removed from their containers, washed in filtered seawater (0.2 µm pore-size filters), and then each of them was placed on an individual inclined sterile glass slide (21 x 7 cm).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"2j67p","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"74ong","text":"  ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[{"key":0,"offset":0,"length":1}],"data":{}},{"key":"66omj","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{"0":{"type":"image","mutability":"","data":{"guid":"6867ACF0334F11EBBDB9A77181714288","height":154,"id":289938,"is_video":false,"legend":{"blocks":[{"data":{},"depth":0,"entityRanges":[],"inlineStyleRanges":[],"key":"1emoh","text":"Fig 1. Sterile glass slide used for pedal mucus collection.","type":"unstyled"}],"entityMap":{}},"mime":"image/jpeg","nestedSelector":null,"original_name":"ProtocolsIO copy.jpg","placeholder":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/public/65d7d33c6e71ff08bd1fb857919395d3461508fd3e9b87a6515cba5ef80cb95c/cseu33an.jpg","shadow":true,"source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i5eu33an.jpg","webp_source":"https://s3.amazonaws.com/protocols-files/files/i5et33an.webp","width":550}}}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"djj9j","text":"As they moved through the glass, filtered seawater was added to the animal pedal to stimulate individual mucus production. The animals moved in the glass slides for a maximum of five minutes and then were removed.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"cdo92","text":"The mucus on the glass slides was removed with a sterile scalpel and put in individual cryovials with filtered seawater.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fqrg5","text":"Then, the experiment consisted of placing the pedal mucus collected from individuals of each species in separate replicated wells with cover glass slides cultured with biofilm. The control wells received no mucus, and pedal mucus treatments were randomly assigned to the cell culture plates.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bfk7h","text":"After one week, we took the cover slides from the cell culture plates separately and stained them with 200 μl 0.01% acridine orange for 3 minutes. The acridine orange is a fluorescent compound that emits red fluorescence when attached to single-stranded templates (RNA) and green fluorescence if the nucleic acids are double-stranded (DNA) (Rigler 1966). It can estimate the total amount of bacterial cells in the biofilm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"bmsn4","text":"After 3 min incubation in the dark, the staining solution was removed, and the plate was washed twice with 500 μl of PBS solution.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"hs3","text":"We took five photographs of each cover glass slide in different fields under a Fluorescent Carl Zeiss AXIO Scope A1 Microscope using an excitation filter (FS38) 470/40 nm and an emission filter 525/50 nm.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}
